+   profraw union. Each program ends in "quit\n" (or fills all 40 bytes and
+   hits EOF) so its branch TERMINATES and emits a ktest; klee_assume records
+   the bytes on the symbolic stdin object (the native cov binary replays them)
+   and buf[i]=p[i] concretizes the lexer buffer so number.c's arithmetic stays
+   concrete (no solver-bound query blowup). Guarded by KLEE_BITCODE so the
+   native coverage binary never sees the klee_assume / klee_range intrinsics. */
+#include <klee/klee.h>
